==Trivia==
*The Kalphite Queen was the first monster to use multiple simultaneous overhead [[protection prayer]] symbols. [[File:Protect from Magic and Missiles overhead.png]]
*The Kalphite Queen was developed by {{RSL|Mod Bennett}}, who also created the outer area of [[Mor Ul Rek]] and the [[TzHaar Fight Cave]]. During development, the Kalphite Queen was considered an extremely difficult boss to kill, as she was able to kill testers even as they used cheats to heal themselves.{{CiteReddit|author=Mod Ash|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/2007scape/comments/1m72il8/comment/n4vrj35/|title=21 Years at Jagex + RuneFest Medley (Deluxe) music video {{!}} AMA|quote=The TzHaar area was made by Mod Bennett, implementer of much of RS2's original combat code, and one of the most technically proficient devs of the 2004-6 era. [...] Mod Bennett made the KQ too, as the first boss that hadn't been in RS Classic. She was considered so hard that testers died even while using cheats to heal themselves. I believe Mod Bennett was trying out the capabilities of the new combat system he'd written, leaning into the different combat styles that wouldn't have existed in the same way in Classic.|date=24 July 2025|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/ISCP2|archivedate=11 October 2025}}
*According to the [[Kalphite Queen head (mounted)]], [[kalphite]]s used to overrun all of [[Gielinor]] before being forced underground.

